.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2025" "Version 1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- A simple Unix command-line interpreter.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a command-line interpreter that mimics the behavior of `/bin/sh`. It reads user input, parses commands, executes programs, and displays output.

.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:
  ./hsh
  ($) /bin/ls
  ($) exit

Non-interactive mode:
  echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh

.SH OPTIONS
The Simple Shell does not currently support any command-line options.

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
The shell uses the `PATH` environment variable to locate executables. If the `PATH` is not set, only absolute or relative paths can be used.

